I"h<h1 id="type-slope_gradient">Type: slope_gradient</h1>

<p>Commonly called ‘slope’. The angle between ground surface and a horizontal line (in percent). This is the direction that overland water would flow. This measure is usually taken with a hand level meter or clinometer</p>

<p>URI: <a href="https://microbiomedata/meta/slope_gradient">nmdc:slope_gradient</a></p>

<h2 id="domain-and-range">Domain and Range</h2>

